<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN289">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>īra cevvi yutaviṉa vāyiṉum</l>
<l>pallerut tuḷḷu nallerutu nōkki</l>
<l>vīṟuvī ṟāyu muḻavaṉ pōlap</l>
<l>pīṭupeṟu tolkuṭi pāṭupala tāṅkiya</l>
<l>mūti lāḷa ruḷḷuṅ kātaliṉ</l>
<l>ṟaṉakku mukantēntiya pacumpoṉ maṇṭai</l>
<l>yivaṟkīka veṉṉu matuvu maṉṟiciṉē</l>
<l>kēṭṭiyō vāḻi pāṇa pācaṟai</l>
<l>pūkkō ḷiṉṟeṉ ṟaṟaiyu</l>
<l>maṭivāyt taṇṇumai yiḻiciṉaṉ kuralē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Like a ploughman who selects the distinctive characteristics,</l>
<l>looking for the [one] good bull among all the many bulls,</l>
<l>even though the [days of] seasonal wetness are [already] helping,</l>
<l>[he] holds out the vessel of green gold after having drawn [it] towards himself,</l>
<l>lovingly(?), [and], among all the men from ancient houses</l>
<l>who have lasted through events many, from ancient families that have obtained greatness,</l>
<l>he says: “please give [it] to him”. Let it not be so(?).</l>
<l>Can you hear it – live, bard –, in the encampment,</l>
<l>the voice of the low-caste man with the Taṇṇumai drum, [its] opening [covered] by leather</l>
<l>that they beat: “today [is] the [time for] taking flowers”.</l>
</lg>
